# Code Style & Structure Rules for Claude

Follow these code style and structural guidelines when working on Konflux UI. These rules extend and complement the existing Cursor rules.

## Import Style & Organization

### ES Modules Only
```tsx
// ✅ Good - ES modules
import { useState } from 'react';
import { Button } from '@patternfly/react-core';

// ❌ Avoid - CommonJS
const React = require('react');
```

### Destructuring Imports
```tsx
// ✅ Good - Destructured imports
import { Button, Card, Flex } from '@patternfly/react-core';
import { useApplications, useComponents } from '~/hooks';

// ❌ Avoid - Default imports when destructuring available
import PatternflyCore from '@patternfly/react-core';
```

### Import Order (from .eslintrc.cjs)
1. React and external libraries
2. PatternFly components
3. Internal imports with ~ alias
4. Relative imports
5. SCSS imports last

```tsx
import * as React from 'react';
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';
import { Button, Card } from '@patternfly/react-core';
import { FlaskIcon } from '@patternfly/react-icons/dist/esm/icons/flask-icon';
import { useApplications } from '~/hooks';
import { MyType } from '~/types';
import './MyComponent.scss';
```

## Code Conventions

### Variable Naming
- **Components**: PascalCase (`NotificationHeader`)
- **Hooks**: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useNotifications`)
- **Variables/Functions**: camelCase (`isLoading`, `handleClick`)
- **Constants**: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`API_ENDPOINT`)
- **Files**: kebab-case (`notification-header.tsx`)

### Function Style
```tsx
// ✅ Prefer arrow functions for components
const NotificationHeader: React.FC<Props> = ({ onClose, notifications }) => {
  return <div>...</div>;
};

// ✅ Use function declarations for utilities
function formatTimestamp(date: string): string {
  return dayjs(date).format('MMM D YYYY');
}
```

### TypeScript Conventions
```tsx
// ✅ Define interfaces for props
interface NotificationHeaderProps {
  onClose: () => void;
  notifications: SystemNotificationConfig[];
}

// ✅ Use union types for variants
type NotificationType = 'info' | 'warning' | 'danger' | 'success';

// ✅ Prefer type inference where possible
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false); // inferred as boolean
```

## File Structure Rules

### Component Organization
```
src/components/MyFeature/
├── MyFeature.tsx           # Main component
├── MyFeature.scss          # Styles (if needed)
├── SubComponent.tsx        # Related sub-components
├── types.ts               # Feature-specific types
├── utils.ts               # Feature-specific utilities
└── __tests__/
    ├── MyFeature.spec.tsx
    └── SubComponent.spec.tsx
```

### When to Create New Files
- **AVOID** creating new files unless absolutely necessary
- **PREFER** editing existing files
- Only create new files for:
  - Major new features with multiple components
  - Completely new pages/routes
  - New utility modules

## Comments and Documentation

### Comment Guidelines
- **DO NOT** add comments unless specifically requested
- **AVOID** explaining obvious code
- **USE** JSDoc for complex utility functions only when needed

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid obvious comments
const [count, setCount] = useState(0); // State for count

// ✅ Only comment complex business logic when needed
// Calculate notifications from past hour for header display
const recentCount = notifications.filter(
  notification => new Date(notification.created) > oneHourAgo
).length;
```

## Performance and Best Practices

### React Patterns
```tsx
// ✅ Use useCallback for event handlers passed to children
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  onAction(id);
}, [onAction, id]);

// ✅ Use useMemo for expensive calculations
const filteredNotifications = useMemo(() => 
  notifications.filter(n => n.type === selectedType),
  [notifications, selectedType]
);

// ✅ Prefer early returns
if (isLoading) {
  return <Spinner />;
}

if (error) {
  return <ErrorState error={error} />;
}

return <MainContent />;
```

### PatternFly Integration
- Always use PatternFly components over custom HTML
- Use PatternFly layout components (Flex, Grid, Stack) instead of divs
- Leverage PatternFly design tokens for consistent spacing and colors
- Follow PatternFly's responsive breakpoint system

## Error Handling

### Error Boundaries and States
```tsx
// ✅ Handle loading and error states
if (isLoading) {
  return <Bullseye><Spinner /></Bullseye>;
}

if (error) {
  const httpError = HttpError.fromCode(error.code);
  return (
    <ErrorEmptyState 
      httpError={httpError}
      title="Unable to load notifications"
      body={error.message}
    />
  );
}
```

These rules ensure consistency with the existing codebase and complement the Cursor rules for styling and project structure.